Citation.sAbstract: The ultrasonic speeds, u and viscosities,  A of binary mixtures of formamide (FA) with 1-butanol, 2-butanol, 1,3-butanediol and 1,4-butanediol,  including those of pure liquids, over the entire composition range were measured at temperatures 293.15, 298.15, 303.15, 308.15, 313.15 and  318.15 K. From the experimental u and  A data, the deviations in isentropic compressibility,  ks, in ultrasonic speed,  u, and in viscosity,   A  were calculated. The partial molar compressibilities,  PKm,1 and  PKm,2 of FA and alkanol in the mixtures over the whole composition range and  PK  .m  ,1  and  PK  .m  ,2 at infinite dilution and excess partial molar compressibilities,  PK  Em  ,1 and  PK  Em  ,2, over the whole composition range and  PK.E  m,1 and  PK.E  m,2 at  infinite dilution were calculated by using two different approaches. The variations of these parameters with composition and temperature of the  mixtures are discussed in terms of molecular interaction in these mixtures. It is observed that the FA-alkanol interactions in these mixtures follows  the order: 1-butanol less than 2-butanol less than 1,3-butanediol less than 1,4-butanediol. The effect of the number and position of the hydroxyl groups in these alkanol  molecules on the molecular interactions in these mixtures is discussed. Furthermore, the free energies,  G*, enthalpies,  H*, and entropies,  S*  of activation of viscous flow have also been obtained by using Eyring viscosity equation. The dependence of  G*,  H* and  S* on composition  of the mixtures have been discussed.
Citation.sTitle: Molecular interactions in binary mixtures of formamide with 1-butanol, 2-butanol, 1,3-butanediol and 1,4-butanediol at different temperatures: An ultrasonic and viscometric study
